The paper proposes a machine learning model for the multi-touch attribution problem in online advertising. The model uses a recurrent neural network with attention mechanisms to learn attribution values from user behavior data. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves predicting user behavior and estimating conversion rates. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques (cs.CL) for sequence-to-sequence prediction. Additionally, the topic of online advertising involves cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and potentially cryptography (cs.CR) for secure data handling.
